msgid "Electrix Tweaker (channel encoder layers)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/electrix_tweaker.md:199
msgid ""
"The encoder layer buttons (#4 and #8 in the diagram) toggle the encoders "
"between EQ and loop layers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/electrix_tweaker.md:202
msgid ""
"The left side of the diagram shows EQ mode. In EQ mode, pressing encoders "
"toggles that EQ’s kill switch. The blue LED below the encoder is lit while "
"the kill switch is on. Pressing the encoder while holding deck shift (see "
"{ref}`deck controls #10 <deck-controls>`) resets the EQ to center."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/electrix_tweaker.md:208
msgid ""
"Tip: You can go to Options > Preferences > Equalizers and check “Reset "
"equalizers on track load”. On most controllers, this would be an issue "
"because the physical knobs would be misaligned with the values in software "
"when the EQs were reset, but because the Tweaker has LED rings around "
"encoders instead of knobs, this is not an issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/electrix_tweaker.md:214
msgid ""
"The right side of the diagram shows loop mode. The LEDs on the loop move "
"length and loop length encoders represent numbers of beats. Center means 1 "
"beat. Each step to the right doubles the beats and each step to the left "
"halves the beats. For example, the default loop length is 4 beats, so the "
"center LED and 2 LEDs to the right are lit (2 x 2 = 4)."
msgstr ""

